01:38:58,423 --> 01:38:59,685
Nivaaranji... Nivaaranji...

1205
01:39:00,091 --> 01:39:02,218
Here speak to Steve.
- Hi Mohan.

1206
01:39:02,427 --> 01:39:06,557
Steve, what about the
geometrical axis function?

1207
01:39:07,098 --> 01:39:11,831
It's being calibrated. The baseline
parameter's been optimized.

1208
01:39:12,270 --> 01:39:17,640
See, the sun-synch orbit needs to be in
alignment with the radiometers of TRMM.

1209
01:39:18,276 --> 01:39:20,574
Ok, I'll make the remaining readings
and call you in a couple of days.

1210
01:39:20,879 --> 01:39:22,141
Ok, thanks.

1211
01:39:22,614 --> 01:39:26,141
Hey Mohan so how's everything else?

1212
01:39:26,451 --> 01:39:28,476
Everything's fine. All is well.

1213
01:39:28,786 --> 01:39:30,754
So, have you found yourself
a village belle?

1214
01:39:31,121 --> 01:39:32,247
Actually, you can say yes.

1215
01:39:32,356 --> 01:39:33,721
What?

1216
01:39:33,958 --> 01:39:36,483
You're kidding me right?
- No.

1217
01:39:37,628 --> 01:39:39,619
What's her name?

1218
01:39:39,964 --> 01:39:43,365
Her name is Gita.
Kaveriamma lives with her.

1219
01:39:43,634 --> 01:39:45,295
I don't believe this!

1220
01:39:45,636 --> 01:39:47,297
Except, she's no village belle...

1221
01:39:47,638 --> 01:39:50,300
She studied in Delhi
and now she runs a school here.

1222
01:39:50,474 --> 01:39:52,772
Have you told her?

1223
01:39:53,143 --> 01:39:54,440
Does she know?

1224
01:39:54,812 --> 01:39:56,780
How can I tell her?
- What do you mean?

1225
01:39:56,981 --> 01:39:58,380
I mean...

1226
01:39:59,149 --> 01:40:04,451
I mean she's got a different set
of ideals et al. She's just different.

1227
01:40:04,822 --> 01:40:07,222
Come on!
You can't make that mistake.

1228
01:40:07,491 --> 01:40:08,958
You have to tell her how you feel.

1229
01:40:09,326 --> 01:40:10,953
All right... if you say so.

1230
01:40:11,161 --> 01:40:13,288
Listen I'll catch up with you later,
gotta go now.

1231
01:40:13,497 --> 01:40:17,160
Your two weeks are almost up!

1232
01:40:17,835 --> 01:40:18,893
I know.

1233
01:40:19,169 --> 01:40:20,295
I'll be back soon.

1234
01:40:20,504 --> 01:40:24,099
You should have been back already.
- But let me propose to her first.

1235
01:40:24,508 --> 01:40:26,908
I'll be leaving soon,
catch up with you later, bye.

1236
01:40:27,044 --> 01:40:28,033
Bye.

1237
01:40:30,180 --> 01:40:32,171
Gurnaamji, how much was that?

1238
01:40:35,185 --> 01:40:38,018
32 minutes. Is it ok if I pay tomorrow?
- Yes.

1239
01:40:38,355 --> 01:40:42,155
My apologies Mohanbabu!
The electricity is problematic here.

1240
01:41:13,557 --> 01:41:15,855
Why are you trying to
corrupt Chikku's mind?

1241
01:41:16,060 --> 01:41:17,687
What are you talking about?

1242
01:41:17,895 --> 01:41:21,353
Haven't you been talking to him and
his friends about going to America?

1243
01:41:21,565 --> 01:41:23,032
No Gita, I was just explaining...

1244
01:41:23,233 --> 01:41:27,533
Am I teaching these kids so that they can
go abroad and settle down like you?

1245
01:41:27,738 --> 01:41:30,798
You NRI. Non-Returning Indian!

1246
01:41:34,578 --> 01:41:36,102
Hand me the mug, please.

1247
01:41:37,581 --> 01:41:40,550
You don't even know how to have a bath.
You should learn from Chikku.

1248
01:41:40,751 --> 01:41:42,218
Gita, I think you need a vacation.

1249
01:41:42,586 --> 01:41:44,850
Why don't you come back
with me for one?

1250
01:41:47,091 --> 01:41:48,888
Gita, you are very mischievous.
Where's the bucket?

1251
01:41:49,093 --> 01:41:50,560
Listen...
- No. You listen to me.

1252
01:41:50,761 --> 01:41:54,561
What?
- I like you very much... Gitli!

1253
01:41:54,932 --> 01:41:56,900
What?!
- It's true, Gitli!

1254
01:41:57,267 --> 01:42:01,863
I liked the way you handled
that man in the bookshop.

1255
01:42:02,206 --> 01:42:06,575
Don't try to sweet talk me.
Kaveriamma will stay here... with me!

1256
01:42:06,776 --> 01:42:09,404
You're misunderstanding.
I really like you.

1257
01:42:09,779 --> 01:42:12,907
Shut up! And don't you try
to corrupt the kids again, ok?

1258
01:42:13,116 --> 01:42:16,381
I'm not corrupting anyone.
I'm only bathing.

1259
01:42:20,056 --> 01:42:23,219
More than the kids, you're the
one who needs an education!

1260
01:42:28,131 --> 01:42:30,531
You can keep calling out to
YOUR Kaveriamma now.

1261
01:42:44,981 --> 01:42:49,475
All right now, remove your notebooks.
The topic is General Knowledge.

1262
01:42:49,819 --> 01:42:51,047
So who's going to tell me...

1263
01:42:51,254 --> 01:42:55,554
...the names of five of the most
important rivers in the country?

1264
01:42:57,427 --> 01:42:59,622
I'm sorry to be late teacher.

1265
01:43:10,106 --> 01:43:11,903
Look ahead.

1266
01:43:16,512 --> 01:43:18,707
Today I'm going to take your class!

1267
01:43:21,184 --> 01:43:22,549
First question...

1268
01:43:22,852 --> 01:43:26,151
...name five main rivers in India?

1269
01:43:27,690 --> 01:43:28,987
You...

1270
01:43:30,693 --> 01:43:31,785
...tell me!

1271
01:43:33,863 --> 01:43:35,160
Let me think.

1272
01:43:37,467 --> 01:43:41,426
Ganga, Jamuna, Narmada...

1273
01:43:44,207 --> 01:43:45,834
...Bharati...

1274
01:43:47,376 --> 01:43:48,502
...Panchgani...

1275
01:43:48,711 --> 01:43:52,977
Bharati? Panchgani?
Are they rivers?

1276
01:43:54,383 --> 01:43:56,044
Vidya, you tell me.

1277
01:43:56,385 --> 01:44:01,186
Ganga, Jamuna, Narmada...
Godavari and Brahmaputra.

1278
01:44:05,495 --> 01:44:06,985
Excellent Vidya!

1279
01:44:08,731 --> 01:44:10,062
Second question...

1280
01:44:10,900 --> 01:44:15,803
...name the new state that has
been formed in North-West India?

1281
01:44:17,240 --> 01:44:21,142
I know this one.
It was a part of Uttar Pradesh, right?

1282
01:44:25,581 --> 01:44:27,139
Yes Chikku. You tell us!

1283
01:44:27,416 --> 01:44:28,883
It's Uttaranchal!
- Oh yes, Uttaranchal!

1284
01:44:29,085 --> 01:44:31,019
How could I have missed it?
I forgot!

1285
01:44:31,921 --> 01:44:33,513
Well done, Chikku!

1286
01:44:34,757 --> 01:44:36,418
Now the last question...

1287
01:44:36,759 --> 01:44:40,286
...if our new student does
not know the answer...

1288
01:44:40,763 --> 01:44:43,664
...we'll have to demote him to
a lower class.

1289
01:44:59,281 --> 01:45:02,341
How many lion heads does
the Ashoka pillar have?

1290
01:45:06,454 --> 01:45:07,887
This one is easy.

1291
01:45:08,290 --> 01:45:09,120
Three.

1292
01:45:09,457 --> 01:45:12,392
Noooooo! It's got four!

1293
01:45:14,963 --> 01:45:17,932
Excellent, children!
The lesson of the day is...

1294
01:45:18,133 --> 01:45:20,101
...before gaining knowledge
about foreign lands,

1295
01:45:20,402 --> 01:45:23,963
it is important that one should
know one's own country first.

1296
01:45:29,477 --> 01:45:31,672
Don't forget to do your homework.

1297
01:45:39,254 --> 01:45:42,690
The rivers Ganga and Jamuna have
their confluence point in Allahabad.

1298
01:45:42,991 --> 01:45:44,754
The new state Uttaranchal...

1299
01:45:44,993 --> 01:45:48,292
...is the 27th state of India
with Dehradun as its capital.

1300
01:45:48,496 --> 01:45:51,294
This is the land where the
Mahabharata was written!

1301
01:45:51,666 --> 01:45:53,861
The Ashoka pillar rests
in a circular abacus,

1302
01:45:54,169 --> 01:45:57,297
which is girded by four animals.
The bull of the West...

1303
01:45:57,606 --> 01:46:05,377
...the elephant of the East,
the horse of the South...

1304
01:46:05,680 --> 01:46:07,580
...and lion by the North.

1305
01:46:11,686 --> 01:46:17,818
Gita, the blackboard is clean.

1306
01:46:25,200 --> 01:46:26,997
Gita... I am...

1307
01:46:31,206 --> 01:46:32,434
Gita...!

1308
01:46:36,711 --> 01:46:38,542
But all my answers were correct.

1309
01:46:39,047 --> 01:46:42,847
This is Natthu, the potter and
this is Shankar...

1310
01:46:43,051 --> 01:46:44,177
...he makes baskets.

1311
01:46:44,386 --> 01:46:48,322
Both of them want us to admit
their children in school.

1312
01:46:48,556 --> 01:46:51,184
What Mohanbabu said to us
the other day touched our hearts.

1313
01:46:51,559 --> 01:46:55,552
We don't want our
children to suffer like us.

1314
01:46:56,064 --> 01:46:58,191
<i>On the morning of Dussehra
(Indian festival)</i>

1315
01:46:58,566 --> 01:47:01,194
you can come and enroll your
children in the school.

1316
01:47:01,403 --> 01:47:03,098
Yes ok.

1317
01:47:07,075 --> 01:47:09,202
The tides have begun to
change direction.

1318
01:47:09,577 --> 01:47:10,976
Haven't they?

1319
01:47:20,588 --> 01:47:22,146
I'm sorry.

1320
01:47:33,100 --> 01:47:35,068
Mohan!- Yes?

1321
01:47:36,437 --> 01:47:40,396
Mohan, I have some work for you.
- What work?

1322
01:47:40,607 --> 01:47:42,734
There's a place called Kodi a
few miles from here.

1323
01:47:43,110 --> 01:47:45,237
Gita has some family property there,

1324
01:47:45,612 --> 01:47:48,080
which has been leased to a
farmer called Haridas.

1325
01:47:48,449 --> 01:47:50,940
He has not paid his rent for
some months.

1326
01:47:51,118 --> 01:47:52,881
I want you to go an
recover the money.

1327
01:47:53,454 --> 01:47:54,580
Me?

1328
01:47:55,456 --> 01:47:57,754
But why do you want me to go?
Can't you send someone else?

1329
01:47:58,058 --> 01:48:01,152
If you go and ask
he just might pay up.

1330
01:48:01,462 --> 01:48:04,329
Oh! So you want me
to be a collector now!

1331
01:48:04,631 --> 01:48:08,795
Ok, when should I leave?
I have to fuel up the caravan.

1332
01:48:09,136 --> 01:48:11,104
You have to leave now.
- Now?

1333
01:48:11,305 --> 01:48:14,763
Yes, and you can't take the caravan there.
- Then?

1334
01:48:15,142 --> 01:48:17,269
You will have to take the train
for three hours to Narsinga...

1335
01:48:17,478 --> 01:48:19,537
...then a boat journey across
the river to Maangaon...

1336
01:48:19,880 --> 01:48:23,111
...and finally three hours by bus...
and you've reached Kodi!

1337
01:48:23,317 --> 01:48:27,879
Sure, that's pretty closeby!
- You'll return by tomorrow evening.

1338
01:48:28,155 --> 01:48:32,387
And Mela Ram will go with you.
He knows the way.

1339
01:48:33,660 --> 01:48:36,026
Kaveriamma...
- Yes?

1340
01:48:37,765 --> 01:48:42,202
My vacation is nearing it's end.
What have you decided?

1341
01:48:43,771 --> 01:48:46,137
You finish this work first.

1342
01:48:51,845 --> 01:48:53,710
Come on Collector saheb...!

1343
01:48:57,684 --> 01:48:59,083
Why are you sending Mohan?

1344
01:48:59,286 --> 01:49:01,982
I sent Haridas a message only
a few days ago.

1345
01:49:03,023 --> 01:49:05,719
I know what I'm doing!

1346
01:49:14,435 --> 01:49:16,995
Good morning sir.
- Good morning Melaram.

1347
01:49:17,204 --> 01:49:20,605
I'm all set to take you on a
sightseeing trip of the village.

1348
01:49:27,214 --> 01:49:28,374
Ok, I'll take your leave.

1349
01:49:28,549 --> 01:49:31,382
Mohanbhaiyya, you'll
bring me a toy, won't you?

1350
01:49:31,552 --> 01:49:34,953
Of course! Gimme five... yes!

1351
01:49:45,065 --> 01:49:47,795
And what shall I bring for you?

1352
01:49:48,235 --> 01:49:49,668
Nothing.

1353
01:49:51,572 --> 01:49:56,532
I know you don't want me to leave,
but I have to go for Kaveriamma.

1354
01:49:57,244 --> 01:50:00,236
And listen, don't think
about me too much.

1355
01:50:00,913 --> 01:50:02,676
Don't miss me too much.

1356
01:50:03,249 --> 01:50:06,685
Now what makes you think
that I'll miss you?

1357
01:50:07,253 --> 01:50:08,686
The look in your eyes!

1358
01:50:10,590 --> 01:50:12,455
They give your feelings away.

1359
01:50:54,133 --> 01:50:56,761
O beloved, most beloved, surely

1360
01:50:56,969 --> 01:51:00,029
I am infatuated with thee

1361
01:51:00,306 --> 01:51:03,434
Thou hast endeared my heart

1362
01:51:03,643 --> 01:51:07,101
O beloved...

1363
01:51:09,982 --> 01:51:12,780
O beloved, most beloved, surely

1364
01:51:13,152 --> 01:51:16,053
I am infatuated with thee

1365
01:51:16,322 --> 01:51:19,450
Thou hast endeared my heart

1366
01:51:19,659 --> 01:51:22,526
O beloved...

1367
01:51:22,762 --> 01:51:25,788
My heart's bewildered

1368
01:51:25,998 --> 01:51:28,967
My body with fire kindled

1369
01:51:29,168 --> 01:51:32,137
It's monsoon of my dreams

1370
01:51:32,338 --> 01:51:35,307
The courtyard of my eyes streams

1371
01:51:35,675 --> 01:51:38,644
The pitcher of my heart is overflowing

1372
01:51:38,844 --> 01:51:45,807
O beloved...

1373
01:52:20,720 --> 01:52:26,590
O dear who hast drawn so near!
O dear who hast endeared my heart!

1374
01:52:26,892 --> 01:52:29,690
How canst I recount

1375
01:52:30,062 --> 01:52:34,158
What hath been thy bequest pray how?

1376
01:52:35,067 --> 01:52:38,036
Somewhere art buds of
a throbbing heart

1377
01:52:38,236 --> 01:52:41,205
Somewhere the dream-lanes

1378
01:52:41,406 --> 01:52:44,375
Mirth that dwells in the heart,

1379
01:52:44,576 --> 01:52:47,204
How shallst I articulate?

1380
01:52:47,412 --> 01:52:50,381
Thou swayeth me so

1381
01:52:50,582 --> 01:52:55,417
That oft times I am embarrassed

1382
01:52:55,620 --> 01:53:01,957
It seems I have lost
my path

1383
01:53:02,160 --> 01:53:08,156
Ever since I have seen the
haven of love

1384
01:53:08,366 --> 01:53:11,199
Haven of love

1385
01:53:11,603 --> 01:53:14,697
O beloved, most beloved,
surely

1386
01:53:14,906 --> 01:53:17,807
I am infatuated with thee

1387
01:53:18,043 --> 01:53:21,103
Thou hast endeared my heart

1388
01:53:21,313 --> 01:53:24,510
O beloved...

1389
01:54:00,485 --> 01:54:06,856
Now that thou hast met me
This world's transformed

1390
01:54:07,058 --> 01:54:13,054
Methinks the flowers have begun
to beset my path

1391
01:54:13,264 --> 01:54:18,759
And I fancy too
That this earth's renewed

1392
01:54:18,970 --> 01:54:26,138
The sky too freshly spun
in our love

1393
01:54:26,478 --> 01:54:29,413
Wanton breeze singeth some melody

1394
01:54:29,614 --> 01:54:34,551
River too narrates some tale

1395
01:54:34,753 --> 01:54:41,090
All's changed, my love
since my eyes courted thine

1396
01:54:41,292 --> 01:54:47,390
I have lost presence of my mind,
gone is my treasured selfhood

1397
01:54:47,599 --> 01:54:51,558
O beloved...

1398
01:55:09,654 --> 01:55:11,622
Haridasji!

1399
01:55:15,994 --> 01:55:17,018
Haridasji!

1400
01:55:17,661 --> 01:55:18,685
Yes?

1401
01:55:23,967 --> 01:55:26,663
I'm Mela Ram and this is
Mohan Bhargavaji.

1402
01:55:27,004 --> 01:55:28,028
Tell me.

1403
01:55:28,172 --> 01:55:32,541
Kaveriji and Gitaji have sent me.
It's about the land's rent.

1404
01:55:34,845 --> 01:55:36,039
I understand.

1405
01:55:36,680 --> 01:55:38,648
Come in.

1406
01:55:45,856 --> 01:55:50,088
You have travelled a long way.
You must be tired. Please rest.

1407
01:55:51,028 --> 01:55:52,962
Make some bread.

1408
01:55:54,031 --> 01:55:55,658
Run along now.

1409
01:55:56,867 --> 01:55:57,959
Please come in.

1410
01:56:15,052 --> 01:56:17,418
You really shouldn't have bothered.

1411
01:56:18,889 --> 01:56:22,586
How is that possible?
A guest is like God!

1412
01:56:23,560 --> 01:56:26,825
We've served what we have;
you eat and then we'll talk.

1413
01:56:27,397 --> 01:56:28,386
Ok.

1414
01:56:42,579 --> 01:56:46,948
If I had the capacity to pay,
I would have come to Charanpur myself.

1415
01:56:47,584 --> 01:56:51,418
Sir, I was a weaver before I
took up farming.

1416
01:56:52,589 --> 01:56:55,057
Since the advent of machine
woven fabrics in the market,

1417
01:56:55,759 --> 01:56:57,693
weaving had ceased to
be a lucrative business.

1418
01:56:58,996 --> 01:57:03,592
So I became a farmer.
I took Gitaji's land on lease.

1419
01:57:05,102 --> 01:57:11,041
I'd imagined, once the crops flourished
the children's life would improve.

1420
01:57:13,110 --> 01:57:14,634
But it was not to be!

1421
01:57:16,446 --> 01:57:17,470
Why?

1422
01:57:18,782 --> 01:57:22,582
By taking up farming,
I had changed my profession.

1423
01:57:23,954 --> 01:57:28,823
The village elders did not accept this
and looked upon me as an outcast.

1424
01:57:30,794 --> 01:57:35,857
They felt a weaver should remain a weaver,
even if it meant, that he had to go hungry.

1425
01:57:37,801 --> 01:57:43,068
I cried, pleaded...
but no one listened to me!

1426
01:57:44,808 --> 01:57:48,869
Nobody offered a drop of
water to irrigate my land.

1427
01:57:51,148 --> 01:57:52,672
Entire crop dried up...

1428
01:57:53,984 --> 01:57:57,750
...and whatever survived,
the villagers refused to buy.

1429
01:57:59,488 --> 01:58:02,514
It is because of this, I've not
been able to pay Gitaji's rent.

1430
01:58:04,660 --> 01:58:05,752
But this is wrong.

1431
01:58:08,831 --> 01:58:12,858
It's unfair. It is an outrage!

1432
01:58:13,336 --> 01:58:15,429
It is the way things work here.

1433
01:58:17,506 --> 01:58:19,371
Not a morsel to
fill our stomach,

1434
01:58:20,509 --> 01:58:24,707
no clothes to wear,
no roof above our heads,

1435
01:58:25,681 --> 01:58:28,445
no education for children,
nor land!

1436
01:58:29,685 --> 01:58:35,248
The thirst in my heart alone
knows the taste of my tears!

1437
01:58:37,860 --> 01:58:39,054
Then what did you do?

1438
01:58:39,528 --> 01:58:40,654
What could I do?

1439
01:58:41,864 --> 01:58:45,595
I thought about migrating to the city,
hoping life would be better there.

1440
01:58:47,370 --> 01:58:50,396
Those who had been there,
recounted the anguish in the cities.

1441
01:58:51,874 --> 01:58:57,335
A labourer goes there to work,
and falls into the grip of contractors.

1442
01:58:59,048 --> 01:59:04,577
He either returns hungry,
or never returns.

1443
01:59:05,888 --> 01:59:09,654
And soon, the wife has to
sell the little land she has.

1444
01:59:10,559 --> 01:59:12,083
No sir, no!

1445
01:59:12,895 --> 01:59:16,763
I couldn't feed my
children in this life...

1446
01:59:18,734 --> 01:59:20,429
...what is to happen after me?

1447
01:59:21,570 --> 01:59:24,630
And about Gitaji's money,

1448
01:59:25,908 --> 01:59:30,709
I have nothing to offer
except helplessness and shame.

1449
01:59:32,415 --> 01:59:33,439
Nothing...

1450
01:59:49,932 --> 01:59:53,732
Thank you for the food, Haridasji.

1451
02:00:30,639 --> 02:00:32,004
Haridasji, I'll take your leave.

1452
02:00:37,645 --> 02:00:41,513
Please don't mind. Here's
some money. Keep it.

1453
02:00:41,983 --> 02:00:46,113
Mohanbabu, it's very kind of you
but I can't accept it.

1454
02:00:46,488 --> 02:00:48,285
Please Haridasji, I want you to keep it.

1455
02:00:48,490 --> 02:00:51,186
When you have it, you can
return it to me.

1456
02:00:51,493 --> 02:00:55,259
But I don't know when I will
be able repay it.

1457
02:00:57,665 --> 02:00:58,689
Don't worry about it.

1458
02:01:01,002 --> 02:01:05,063
Here Chotu, this is for you.
Share it with your sisters.

1459
02:01:08,009 --> 02:01:12,708
Please give Gitaji
and Kaveriji my respects.

1460
02:02:43,438 --> 02:02:54,246
Water for sale... water for sale...
25 paise for a glass...

1461
02:03:03,458 --> 02:03:07,827
25 paise for a glass of water...

1462
02:03:08,796 --> 02:03:10,320
Saheb, please have a glass of water.

1463
02:05:02,242 --> 02:05:03,709
Mohan you're back!

1464
02:05:11,752 --> 02:05:13,310
How was your journey?

1465
02:05:14,588 --> 02:05:16,852
Ok.
- Did you meet Haridas?

1466
02:05:17,758 --> 02:05:20,625
Yes. But I could not get the money.

1467
02:05:25,098 --> 02:05:29,626
His situation is pathetic.
He can't pay the rent!

1468
02:05:29,936 --> 02:05:33,394
Instead, sir gave him money
from his own pocket, before leaving.

1469
02:05:35,442 --> 02:05:37,637
I couldn't bear to see
Haridas' condition.

1470
02:05:40,947 --> 02:05:43,279
I don't think you should expect
any rent from him.

1471
02:05:45,952 --> 02:05:48,045
Mohanbhaiyya, did you get me my toy?

1472
02:05:51,791 --> 02:05:53,349
I couldn't get anything.

1473
02:05:57,296 --> 02:05:58,490
Come Chikku.

1474
02:06:06,472 --> 02:06:09,441
Mohan this is the general
state of affairs.

1475
02:06:10,976 --> 02:06:14,571
What is money when compared
with the value of human life?

1476
02:06:15,981 --> 02:06:18,506
I'm glad you gave him money.

1477
02:06:19,652 --> 02:06:24,351
Now don't get disheartened.
Rest a little.

1478
02:06:38,904 --> 02:06:40,030
Kaveriamma...

1479
02:06:41,674 --> 02:06:43,505
...how do I wrap this around?

1480
02:06:49,014 --> 02:06:51,539
Kaveriamma has left for school.
For the decorations.

1481
02:06:52,017 --> 02:06:54,918
I don't know why she wants
me to wear this dhoti?

1482
02:06:55,187 --> 02:06:56,882
What's wrong with my jeans anyway?

1483
02:06:57,022 --> 02:06:59,991
It is the appropriate thing to
wear on Dussehra.

1484
02:07:00,192 --> 02:07:01,523
If you wish I can tie it for you.

1485
02:07:01,694 --> 02:07:04,162
How do you know?
Have you ever worn one?

1486
02:07:04,363 --> 02:07:05,830
It's not a saree, ok!

1487
02:07:06,198 --> 02:07:08,063
Ok then! Do it yourself.

1488
02:07:08,200 --> 02:07:12,227
All right, all right.
Just do it quick.

1489
02:07:12,705 --> 02:07:13,729
Come...

1490
02:07:18,377 --> 02:07:19,401
Give...

1491
02:07:21,547 --> 02:07:22,571
Hold it.

1492
02:07:40,733 --> 02:07:42,132
What the...

1493
02:08:20,606 --> 02:08:22,039
There, it's done.

1494
02:08:25,611 --> 02:08:27,101
Sure, it's done...

1495
02:08:27,612 --> 02:08:31,013
...but I hope it doesn't
unravel in a crowd! Or else...

1496
02:08:31,216 --> 02:08:32,240
Shut up!

1497
02:08:35,119 --> 02:08:38,577
Today is the auspicious day of Dussehra.
It was on this day that Lord Rama...

1498
02:08:38,790 --> 02:08:43,921
had slain Ravana and marked the
triumph of good over evil!

1499
02:08:44,128 --> 02:08:50,397
I am very happy that on this day
we initiate new students in the school.

1500
02:09:02,146 --> 02:09:03,613
May the Goddess of Knowledge
be with you.

1501
02:09:03,815 --> 02:09:05,077
It's Lajwa.

1502
02:09:13,324 --> 02:09:16,020
This is our little granddaughter Kusum!

1503
02:09:20,832 --> 02:09:22,697
Now, go and play.

1504
02:09:27,505 --> 02:09:33,102
Mohanji, where are you off?
Why don't you spend some time with us?

1505
02:09:34,846 --> 02:09:37,974
I'm impressed. How well you've
tied your dhoti Mohanbabu?

1506
02:09:38,182 --> 02:09:39,979
How did you manage to learn so quickly?

1507
02:09:40,184 --> 02:09:42,652
It's pretty easy. It was tied in seconds.

1508
02:09:42,854 --> 02:09:44,549
You're looking like a bridegroom.

1509
02:09:47,258 --> 02:09:48,054
Thank you.

1510
02:09:48,192 --> 02:09:52,288
So how long have you lived abroad?

1511
02:09:52,530 --> 02:09:54,828
It's been almost twelve years now.

1512
02:09:55,033 --> 02:09:57,900
You must have adapted yourself
completely to their way of living?

1513
02:09:59,203 --> 02:10:04,664
We would also like to know a
thing or two about America.

1514
02:10:05,209 --> 02:10:10,044
Well... America is a big country...

1515
02:10:10,214 --> 02:10:14,173
We've heard that it's also very rich?

1516
02:10:14,552 --> 02:10:17,817
Rich it is. But there are several
reasons for that.

1517
02:10:18,056 --> 02:10:22,493
One among them is that their land
is rich in mineral resources...

1518
02:10:22,727 --> 02:10:26,060
Even our land is rich, but in crops.

1519
02:10:26,230 --> 02:10:28,824
Our strength... lies in our fields.

1520
02:10:29,233 --> 02:10:31,201
Do they have problems of rain?

1521
02:10:31,402 --> 02:10:34,860
Are they affected by drought
and famine like us?

1522
02:10:35,073 --> 02:10:36,870
And what about electricity?

1523
02:10:40,578 --> 02:10:44,378
They've set up infrastructure to provide
all the basic amenities to the common man.

1524
02:10:44,582 --> 02:10:50,646
Electricity, housing board, healthy
food and free education.

1525
02:10:50,855 --> 02:10:58,227
We have one thing,
they don't have and will never have.

1526
02:10:59,597 --> 02:11:00,621
What?

1527
02:11:01,099 --> 02:11:03,397
Culture and tradition!

1528
02:11:03,601 --> 02:11:04,761
Yes, agreed.

1529
02:11:04,936 --> 02:11:10,738
And till we have that,
no one can destroy us.

1530
02:11:11,108 --> 02:11:14,737
Ours is the greatest country in the world!

1531
02:11:15,278 --> 02:11:16,074
Absolutely!

1532
02:11:16,279 --> 02:11:21,478
Culture and tradition is our strength,
don't you agree?

1533
02:11:25,455 --> 02:11:26,752
Munishwar...

1534
02:11:27,958 --> 02:11:32,657
I don't think... Mohanbabu agrees!

1535
02:11:32,796 --> 02:11:33,990
Do you Mohanji?

1536
02:11:34,965 --> 02:11:36,159
You're right.

1537
02:11:37,134 --> 02:11:40,160
I don't agree that ours is the greatest
country in the world!

1538
02:11:44,641 --> 02:11:49,840
But I do believe that we have the
potential and strength to become great.

1539
02:11:51,982 --> 02:11:56,919
Both these countries are economically,
sociologically and culturally apart.

1540
02:11:57,654 --> 02:12:02,114
I shouldn't say this but since you have
broached this topic, let me say that...

1541
02:12:02,993 --> 02:12:05,587
...whenever we suspect losing
in comparison...

1542
02:12:05,996 --> 02:12:08,260
...we clutch on to our favourite refuge...

1543
02:12:09,666 --> 02:12:10,655
...culture...

1544
02:12:11,334 --> 02:12:12,665
...and tradition!

1545
02:12:13,870 --> 02:12:15,895
America has progressed
on its own strengths.

1546
02:12:16,006 --> 02:12:17,974
They have their own culture
and own tradition.

1547
02:12:18,175 --> 02:12:21,303
It would be wrong to claim
that their culture

1548
02:12:21,511 --> 02:12:24,708
their tradition and beliefs
are inferior and ours are laudable.

1549
02:12:25,515 --> 02:12:26,709
It's wrong.

1550
02:12:28,485 --> 02:12:30,578
But I have heard that

1551
02:12:30,787 --> 02:12:36,453
there they discriminate against
members of ethnic races.

1552
02:12:36,693 --> 02:12:40,151
Yes! There are clashes sometimes.
Aren't they everywhere?

1553
02:12:40,363 --> 02:12:44,732
What is important to analyze is that
we make differences based on caste.

1554
02:12:46,736 --> 02:12:54,438
You talk as if we have created the caste,
class, religion and the social system.

1555
02:12:54,945 --> 02:12:58,938
This hierarchy of caste is ancient
as is culture and religion.

1556
02:12:59,583 --> 02:13:02,017
And colour and creed.

1557
02:13:02,219 --> 02:13:06,349
Remember, one's caste is
a thing that can never die!

1558
02:13:06,556 --> 02:13:09,684
Just because a custom is ancient,
it does not have to be right.

1559
02:13:11,061 --> 02:13:15,361
Why are you imposing your
views on us Mohanbabu?

1560
02:13:16,333 --> 02:13:18,392
I am not imposing any views.

1561
02:13:18,735 --> 02:13:23,035
I am only speaking of things I've
experienced while living here.

1562
02:13:23,807 --> 02:13:26,367
And I've realized that we keep
fighting amongst ourselves...

1563
02:13:26,476 --> 02:13:31,038
...when we must fight against illiteracy,
over-population and corruption.

1564
02:13:31,314 --> 02:13:36,047
Every day, in our streets and homes,
each one of us keeps saying

1565
02:13:36,386 --> 02:13:40,652
"The country has gone to dogs. The
country is on the path of destruction!"

1566
02:13:41,157 --> 02:13:45,218
If we keep saying this, we will
one day actually land up there.

1567
02:13:45,427 --> 02:13:47,156
You'll need to do
something to remedy this.

1568
02:13:47,263 --> 02:13:48,560
You too!

1569
02:13:48,764 --> 02:13:51,426
Not just the members of the Panchayat
but everyone in the village.

1570
02:13:53,035 --> 02:13:56,198
You are blaming the members of the
Panchayat for your problems.

1571
02:13:56,505 --> 02:14:01,568
But when you step into their shoes, you'll
do the same thing. This applies to me too!

1572
02:14:02,478 --> 02:14:04,275
The dalits blame the brahmins...

1573
02:14:04,413 --> 02:14:08,144
...and brahmins claim that their
piety is despoiled by the dalits.

1574
02:14:08,784 --> 02:14:12,083
The blacksmith and potter blame
the moneylender.

1575
02:14:13,088 --> 02:14:16,717
The land owners blame the peasants,
but they don't give them their rights.

1576
02:14:17,626 --> 02:14:20,754
In what way are we great then?

1577
02:14:21,430 --> 02:14:23,694
If we have problems in the village,
we point our finger at the State...

1578
02:14:23,899 --> 02:14:28,666
...and the State at someone else.
We all are finding fault with each other!

1579
02:14:29,104 --> 02:14:32,540
The fact is that we're all to be blamed.

1580
02:14:33,142 --> 02:14:35,610
Because the problem... is us!

1581
02:14:35,945 --> 02:14:38,038
Me... you...

1582
02:14:39,114 --> 02:14:40,604
...all of us!

1583
02:14:41,383 --> 02:14:45,251
Have you lost your head?
What are you saying?

1584
02:14:45,955 --> 02:14:47,547
All I know is that...

1585
02:14:48,591 --> 02:14:52,925
...a weaver who changed his
occupation by becoming a farmer...

1586
02:14:54,163 --> 02:14:57,360
...cannot feed his family

1587
02:14:59,368 --> 02:15:02,098
or give his children an education.

1588
02:15:03,072 --> 02:15:06,439
He can only watch his kids
die of malnutrition.

1589
02:15:52,955 --> 02:15:59,190
Every moment weighs terribly,
we're beset with a calamity

1590
02:15:59,795 --> 02:16:06,200
O scion of Raghu race,
come to rescue me

1591
02:16:07,202 --> 02:16:11,639
Come, O Raghu stalwart,
O lord, I beseech thee

1592
02:16:11,840 --> 02:16:15,970
Adorable lord of my heart,
O my good Ram, appear

1593
02:16:16,178 --> 02:16:20,808
I recite thy Name,
hear thou O Ram and come

1594
02:16:21,016 --> 02:16:22,984
I recite thy Name,

1595
02:16:23,184 --> 02:16:26,881
hear thou O Ram and come

1596
02:16:27,088 --> 02:16:28,953
Proclaim glory of truth
by beat of drum,

1597
02:16:29,390 --> 02:16:31,551
burn Lanka of sins

1598
02:16:31,826 --> 02:16:36,559
At once come, rescue me and
heed loud proclamation mine

1599
02:16:36,764 --> 02:16:43,101
Every moment weighs terribly,
we're beset with a calamity

1600
02:16:43,604 --> 02:16:49,873
O scion of Raghu race,
come to rescue me

1601
02:16:59,821 --> 02:17:03,757
Forget Ram, look!
It's Ravana who hast come

1602
02:17:03,991 --> 02:17:08,325
His mighty shadow hath
spread over all quarters

1603
02:17:08,663 --> 02:17:14,329
Why dost thou recite Name of Ram?
Why dost thou sing rosary of Ram?

1604
02:17:14,635 --> 02:17:18,765
This Ram - Ram thou hast
begun by rote

1605
02:17:18,973 --> 02:17:20,235
O Sita!

1606
02:17:20,441 --> 02:17:24,468
what virtue didst thou
see in Ram to quote?

1607
02:17:25,079 --> 02:17:28,981
Who can recount all His virtues?

1608
02:17:29,217 --> 02:17:33,745
Lexicon too falleth short

1609
02:17:34,255 --> 02:17:38,214
Who can reach the summits

1610
02:17:38,459 --> 02:17:42,896
Where my adorable Ram sits

1611
02:17:43,431 --> 02:17:47,800
Ram is most excellent in this world,
unswerving in virtue

1612
02:17:48,002 --> 02:17:52,234
Most puissant yet
possessed of restraint

1613
02:17:52,440 --> 02:17:56,638
But now his restraint too
hath suffered diminution

1614
02:17:56,844 --> 02:18:01,372
O Ravana! It's not too
late to beg for mercy!

1615
02:18:01,849 --> 02:18:03,441
May the glory of truth be
proclaimed by beat of drum!

1616
02:18:03,851 --> 02:18:05,910
Lanka of sins shouldst burn

1617
02:18:06,220 --> 02:18:08,347
Here cometh Ram; we bow unto Him

1618
02:18:08,556 --> 02:18:10,854
Accompanied by noble
brother Lakshmana

1619
02:18:11,058 --> 02:18:17,258
Every moment weighs terribly,
we're beset with a calamity

1620
02:18:18,099 --> 02:18:27,406
O scion of Raghu race,
come to rescue me

1621
02:18:31,212 --> 02:18:35,046
Shouldst Ram possess strength;
shouldst He valour proclaim

1622
02:18:35,283 --> 02:18:39,185
Why hast He not come to rescue thee,
thy fame?

1623
02:18:39,387 --> 02:18:43,187
He whose glories thou
singeth untiring

1624
02:18:43,391 --> 02:18:47,691
Pray, where is that Ram at
this moment, uncaring?

1625
02:19:03,577 --> 02:19:07,377
Ram resides in mine heart;
Ram is mine breathing part

1626
02:19:07,581 --> 02:19:12,678
Ram is soul mine,
Ram doth my life define

1627
02:19:13,653 --> 02:19:17,384
Ram in all my moments liveth,
it's Ram in every breath

1628
02:19:17,591 --> 02:19:22,255
Ram is in every hope of mine;
Ram is in every wish and pine

1629
02:19:25,699 --> 02:19:29,567
Ram verily in compassion stayeth,
in peace too dwelleth Ram

1630
02:19:29,769 --> 02:19:34,172
Ram for sure in unity is,
progress too is glory His

1631
02:19:35,742 --> 02:19:39,576
Ram, in contemplation of devotees,
and of enemies alike liveth

1632
02:19:39,779 --> 02:19:43,545
Forsake sin, O Ravana! And thou
shalt find Ram in thy heart

1633
02:19:43,750 --> 02:19:47,652
Ram in thy heart,
Ram is in mine heart

1634
02:19:47,854 --> 02:19:51,585
Ram in thy heart,
Ram is in mine heart

1635
02:19:51,791 --> 02:19:55,750
Ram in every home and abode,
Ram at every threshold

1636
02:19:56,062 --> 02:20:00,726
Whoever shouldst oust Ravana
from the heart, to him doth Ram dart

1637
02:20:03,036 --> 02:20:10,568
Whoever shouldst oust Ravana
from the heart, to him doth Ram dart

1638
02:20:20,820 --> 02:20:26,781
Every moment weighs terribly,
we're beset with a calamity

1639
02:20:27,594 --> 02:20:36,525
O scion of Raghu race,
come to rescue me

1640
02:20:43,076 --> 02:20:47,945
Look Lord Ram has come,
Mine Lord Ram has come

1641
02:20:48,148 --> 02:20:52,642
Here comes the scion of the Raghu race,
Here he comes to rescue me

1642
02:20:52,852 --> 02:20:57,016
Look Lord Ram has come,
Mine Lord Ram has come

1643
02:20:57,223 --> 02:21:11,900
Here comes the scion of the Raghu race,
Here he comes to rescue me

1644
02:22:07,359 --> 02:22:11,693
<i>Siyavar Ramchandra Ki... Jai!
(Glory unto Lord Ramchandra)</i>

1645
02:22:31,450 --> 02:22:35,853
The burning Ravan is looking
prettier in the darkness.

1646
02:23:10,923 --> 02:23:14,518
Every moment weighs terribly,
we're beset with a calamity

1647
02:23:14,726 --> 02:23:17,354
Quiet! Please be quiet!

1648
02:23:18,831 --> 02:23:20,423
Why do I feel that...

1649
02:23:20,933 --> 02:23:23,959
...all of you have started
enjoying living in this darkness?

1650
02:23:24,503 --> 02:23:26,368
You've adjusted to this darkness?

1651
02:23:27,539 --> 02:23:32,499
For how long are you'll going to
take your problems lying down?

1652
02:23:34,513 --> 02:23:37,038
But what else can we do, Mohanji?

1653
02:23:37,549 --> 02:23:39,915
Will you do as I ask?

1654
02:23:40,185 --> 02:23:43,712
Have you once again come up
with some strange solution?

1655
02:23:43,989 --> 02:23:45,820
Please have mercy on us!

1656
02:23:47,659 --> 02:23:49,126
Wait Munishwar...

1657
02:23:49,995 --> 02:23:51,394
What do you want us to do?

1658
02:23:51,997 --> 02:23:54,056
Is there a spring on
the nearby mountain?

1659
02:23:54,266 --> 02:23:56,325
Yes there is. So?

1660
02:23:56,535 --> 02:23:58,332
I need a hundred men.

1661
02:23:58,737 --> 02:24:00,671
A hundred men?

1662
02:24:01,039 --> 02:24:02,666
You shall have them.

1663
02:24:03,408 --> 02:24:05,740
You shall have a
hundred men!

1664
02:24:06,478 --> 02:24:07,604
Thank you Dadaji.

1665
02:24:10,983 --> 02:24:14,180
Sir, one hears lightning had struck
this spot several years ago.

1666
02:24:14,386 --> 02:24:16,251
Since then there has been
this gush of water.

1667
02:24:40,578 --> 02:24:43,206
Wonder what he's upto!

1668
02:24:46,083 --> 02:24:50,782
This is Point A1

1669
02:24:53,758 --> 02:24:56,556
We shall build a reservoir here.

1670
02:24:56,928 --> 02:24:58,896
I mean a water tank.

1671
02:24:59,096 --> 02:25:01,360
The water will be
acccumulated here.

1672
02:25:01,766 --> 02:25:05,793
From here, there will be a water pipe
which leads to Point A3.

1673
02:25:06,437 --> 02:25:11,534
A3 will have a shed with a turbine,
I mean a machine.

1674
02:25:11,776 --> 02:25:15,837
When the water falls on the turbine,
it will rotate with great speed.

1675
02:25:16,113 --> 02:25:20,846
And if all things go right,
electricity will be generated.

1676
02:25:26,324 --> 02:25:27,484
We'll form four groups.

1677
02:25:27,625 --> 02:25:30,253
The blacksmiths will cast the moulds.

1678
02:25:30,461 --> 02:25:34,420
The 2nd and 3rd group will do the
